data-triple-N3.o: "Sufism or tasawwuf is defined by its adherents as the inner, mystical dimension of Islam. A practitioner of this tradition is generally known as a sufi (). They belong to different turuq or "orders"congregations formed around a masterwhich meet for spiritual sessions (majalis), in meeting places known as zawiyahs, Khanqahs, or tekke."@en
